The paper discusses the state of the art contributions for online scheduling of jobs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the optimization criterion of makespan minimization, which is a common problem in combinatorial optimization and falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper discusses competitive analysis results obtained by deterministic and randomized algorithms, which are common in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG, cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses emerging trends in online scheduling, which involve optimization and control of robotic systems (cs.RO).
